# Project Title :- API-using-any-Python-Web-Framework-


## Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed before running the application:

- Python 
- Pip (package installer for Python)
- Git (optional, if you want to clone the repository)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
    ```

    Alternatively, download the ZIP file and extract it.

2. Navigate to the project directory:

    ```bash
    cd your-repo
    ```

3. Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):

    ```bash
    python -m venv venv
    ```

4. Activate the virtual environment:

    - On Windows:

        ```bash
        .\venv\Scripts\activate
        ```

    - On Unix or MacOS:

        ```bash
        source venv/bin/activate
        ```

5. Install dependencies:

    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

## Usage

Run the application using the following command:

```bash
python app.py


The application will be accessible at http://127.0.0.1:5000/.

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
----------------------*Endpoints*--------------------
*Add UserProject Entry:*

Method: POST

Endpoint: /add_user_project

Request Body:

json

{
    "user_id": 1,
    "project_name": "ABC project"
}

Add TaskProject Entry:

Method: POST
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
*Endpoint: /add_task_project*

Request Body:

json

{
    "user_project_id": 1,
    "task_id": 1
}

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
Get TaskProject Entry:

Method: GET
Endpoint: /get_task_project/<int:user_id>
Example Response:

json

{
    "User_id": 1,
    "User_name": "abc",
    "Project_id": 2,
    "Project_name": "23",
    "Task_id": 1,
    "Task_name": "3"
}
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

